3. An opto-acoustic bio-transducer for single-cell probing
In the experiments presented in the previous section, biological samples were placed onto a biometallic half-space to generate acoustic waves through the absorption of laser pulses at the sample-metal interface [22,23]. This configuration has allowed the direct determination of the sound velocity and attenuation in single cells at GHz frequencies through the Brillouin acousto-optic
